  "prompt": "In Japanese, what is the meaning of \"Kimigayo\"?",
  "response": "\"Kimigayo\" (\u541b\u304c\u4ee3) is the title of the national anthem of Japan. The phrase \"Kimigayo\" can be translated to English as \"His Majesty's Reign\" or \"The Emperor's Reign.\" The lyrics of the anthem express a wish for the long life and prosperity of the Emperor. Here is the full text of the anthem in Japanese, followed by an English translation:\n\n**Japanese:**\n\u541b\u304c\u4ee3\u306f\n\u5343\u4ee3\u306b\u516b\u5343\u4ee3\u306b\n\u7d30\u77f3\u306e\n\u5dcc\u3068\u306a\u308a\u3066\n\u82d4\u306e\u751f\u3059\u307e\u3067\n\n**English Translation:**\nMay your reign\nContinue for a thousand, eight thousand generations,\nUntil the pebbles\nGrow into boulders\nCovered with moss.\n\nThe anthem is relatively short and traditionally sung in a slow and solemn manner.",
